    "key_findings": [
        "The 2.1 \u00c5 cryo-EM structure of the M5 mAChR, co-bound with acetylcholine and the positive allosteric modulator VU6007678, reveals a novel extrahelical allosteric binding site at the interface between transmembrane domains 3 and 4.",
        "This structure completes the active-state structural characterization of the M5 mAChR, the last remaining subtype of the mAChR family, providing structural insights into its allosteric regulation.",
        "The identified allosteric binding site for VU6007678 is distant from the orthosteric site and interacts with key activation motifs and G protein interactions, indicating that PAM binding stabilizes the active state of the M5 mAChR."
